article.headline: Kent St. 80, Lehigh 75
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Justin Greene and Rodriguez Sherman each scored 18 points as Kent State came from behind to beat Lehigh 80-75 and win its fourth straight on Friday night. The Golden Flashes (6-1) trailed 41-38 at halftime thanks to a 16-for-35 shooting effort (45.7 percent) from the Mountain Hawks. Lehigh couldn't hold the lead in the second half despite C.J. McCollum scoring 24 of his career-high 42 points after intermission. McCollum shot 8 for 13 from the floor (61.5 percent) in the second half, but it wasn't enough as the Golden Flashes outscored Lehigh in second-chance points 16-0, finishing 24-4 in second-chance points for the game. Kent State took the lead, 52-51, at the 12:05 mark and didn't trail the rest of the way -- leading by as many as six -- in a game that saw 11 ties and 22 lead changes. Greene added a game-high 11 rebounds to complete the double-double.
